          "body": "The sayings in 4:21-25 are easy to skip but they tighten the chapter's pastoral force. The lamp (4:21-22) is brought to be seen — the kingdom that is now hidden will inevitably be revealed; the parable's concealment is temporary, not permanent. The measure (4:24-25) is the chapter's stark warning to those who hear: *by your standard of measure it will be measured to you; and more will be given you besides. For whoever has, to him more shall be given; and whoever does not have, even what he has shall be taken away from him.* Receptive hearing compounds; resistant hearing impoverishes. There is no neutral middle. The believer who attends carefully to what God has revealed will be given more revelation; the one who is casual will lose even what they thought they had. Mark places these sayings between the sower-parable and the growth-parables to enforce the demand: *take care what you listen to* (4:24)."
